It adds an easy-bake layer of powerful emotion to artistic depictions of sex scenes like this. Sex alone is one thing, but any visual implication that your subjects are in a deeper partnership tantalizes a subset of imperative/instinctive needs & emotions that're hard-coded in (most) every adult psyche. Thus, symbols of marital bonding in sex scenes scratch more than just the libidinal itch.

>>41769032
Agnosticism is less its own 'belief' and more a broad category that's extant for gray-area ontological meandering & deism. These days, anyway, people are less inclined toward hard-A atheism given its tendency to segue into nihilistic languish. Agnosticism is more amble whereas atheism is either content or disturbed by the bed it makes for itself.
